Top 10 Blockchain Technologies, Users, Purpose, and Tokens

1.Bitcoin
Used by: Individuals, investors, payment companies
Built for: Peer-to-peer digital money
Token: BTC
Token use: Payments, store of value, transaction fees

2.Ethereum
Used by: Developers, DeFi apps, NFT platforms
Built for: Smart contracts & decentralized apps
Token: ETH
Token use: Gas fees for transactions and smart contracts

3.BNB Chain
Used by: Crypto traders, DeFi apps
Built for: Fast and low-cost DeFi transactions
Token: BNB
Token use: Gas fees, staking, exchange utility

4.Solana
Used by: NFT projects, gaming apps, DeFi
Built for: High-speed and low-cost apps
Token: SOL
Token use: Transaction fees, staking, governance

5.Polygon
Used by: Ethereum developers, gaming companies
Built for: Scaling Ethereum
Token: MATIC/POL
Token use: Gas fees, staking, network security

6.Ripple (XRP Ledger)
Used by: Banks, payment providers
Built for: Cross-border payments
Token: XRP
Token use: Fast international transfers

7.Cardano
Used by: Researchers, developers, governments
Built for: Secure smart contracts
Token: ADA
Token use: Staking, governance, fees

8.Polkadot
Used by: Blockchain developers
Built for: Connect multiple blockchains
Token: DOT
Token use: Governance, staking

9.Avalanche
Used by: DeFi platforms, enterprises
Built for: Fast smart contracts
Token: AVAX
Token use: Fees, staking, security

10.Hyperledger Fabric
Used by: IBM, enterprises, banks
Built for: Private enterprise blockchain
Token: No native token
Token use: Supply chain & business transactions


Blockchain	Built For	Main Users	Token & Use

Bitcoin	Digital money	Public, investors	BTC – Payments, store of value
Ethereum	Smart contracts	Developers, DeFi	ETH – Gas fees, apps
Solana	Fast transactions	DeFi, NFT users	SOL – Fees, staking
BNB Chain	Exchange ecosystem	Binance users	BNB – Fees, trading
Cardano	Secure smart contracts	Developers	ADA – Fees, staking
Polygon	Scaling Ethereum	Web3 apps	MATIC – Low fees
Ripple (XRP)	Bank transfers	Banks, finance	XRP – Fast payments
Polkadot	Connect blockchains	Web3 builders	DOT – Staking, governance
Avalanche	DeFi & apps	Developers	AVAX – Fees, staking
Tron	Content & DeFi	Creators	TRX – Payments, fees



